Sentencas: The electroactivity of surfactant-templated mesoporous yttria stabilized zirconia, containing nanoclusters of platinum or nickel oxide, is explored by alternating current (AC) complex impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Electroactive mesoporous yttria stabilized zirconia containing platinum or nickel oxide nanoclusters: A new class of solid oxide fuel cell electrode materials

Sentencas: The observed oxygen ion and mixed oxygen ion-electron charge-transport behavior for these: materials, compared to the sintered-densified non-porous crystalline versions, is ascribed to the unique integration of mesoporosity and nanocrystallinity within the binary and ternary solid solution microstructure.
Titulo: Electroactive mesoporous yttria stabilized zirconia containing platinum or nickel oxide nanoclusters: A new class of solid oxide fuel cell electrode materials

Sentencas: These attributes inspire interest in this new class of materials as candidates for the development of improved performance solid oxide fuel cell electrodes.
Titulo: Electroactive mesoporous yttria stabilized zirconia containing platinum or nickel oxide nanoclusters: A new class of solid oxide fuel cell electrode materials
